General interval comment: Green band at 99cm. Color gradation from brownish color at the top of the section to a lighter gray hue (GLEY 1 7/5GY) before the ash layer.
Green band at 44 cm and dark gray band at 73 cm. Dark green patch on the right hand side at 39 cm. Color gradation to lighter gray colors (GLEY 1 8/10Y) towards bottom of section.
Color gradation to a darker gray color (5Y 5/1) towards bottom of core potentially related to glacial-interglacial cycles.
Color gradation to a lighter gray color (GLEY 1 7/10Y) towards bottom of core potentially related to glacial-interglacial cycles. Green bands at 139-140 and 145-147 cm.

Color gradation to a lighter gray color (GLEY 1 7/10Y) towards bottom of core potentially related to glacial-interglacial cycles. Green bands at 18, 129, and 139 cm. Mottling more pronounced in lighter gray layer. 1 cm diameter nodule at 36 cm.
Color gradation to a darker gray color (5Y 5/1) towards bottom of core potentially related to glacial-interglacial cycles. Mottling more pronounced in darker sediment.
